TextBody:
Hello,

Can you please collect a set of logs following the steps below?

1. Download the archive to an empty folder at the following link:
 https://download.endpointprotector.com/Support_files/support_tool/SupportTool_win.zip
2. Unzip the sub-archive that corresponds to the operating system of the client computer concerned.
3. Double-click the EPPSupportTool_64 or _32.exe file. This opens a dialog box.
4.a. Select Create Log file and click Execute.
4.b. Select Create DPI Log file and click Execute.
4.c. Select Create Appended Log file and click Execute.
This creates a file called eppclient.log and sslsplit.log in the root directory of the C: drive.
5. Right-click the EPP client and click "Update Policies Now".
6. Restart the computer.
7. Right-click the EPP client and click "Update Policies Now".
8. Confirm the service is stopping.
9. Open EPPSupportTool and click Export Files. This will copy files to the current folder.
10. Send me the created files (archived) so that we can investigate them further.

Kind regards
__________________
Andrei Pop | Technical Support Engineer
Netwrix Endpoint Protector
